## Slice 6 — Report card approval workflow (PLANNING + cp1)

Plan-first, all 9 questions answered, then cp1 built. NOT committed — reported
back for review.

### Decisions (the 9 Q&A, banked)
- **Q1 SUBJECT_REVIEWED denominator:** measured against EXISTING Assessment rows
  for (term, arm) — "≥1 assessment and none unsigned". Curriculum coverage NOT
  enforced here (an unscored subject has no row; form-review re-runs the same
  predicate where it matters).
- **Q3 Immutability scope:** RELEASED-only. Edits in SUBJECT_REVIEWED /
  FORM_REVIEWED / PRINCIPAL_APPROVED are allowed; workflow transitions re-check
  preconditions inside the tx to handle races (matches the spec hard rule + the
  race example).
- **Q-rebuild Build guard:** stricter than the edit gate — `build` 409s
  (`ARM_NOT_DRAFT`) when ANY card in the arm is non-DRAFT. Rebuild mid-workflow
  requires reopen → DRAFT first. Protects the "all cards in an arm share a
  status" invariant (a naive rebuild would mix DRAFT new-students with advanced
  cards).
- **Q5 Comment matrix (cp2):** formTeacherComment editable in DRAFT,
  SUBJECT_REVIEWED; principalNote editable in FORM_REVIEWED; all else blocked.
- **Q4 Comment endpoints (cp2):** split — `PATCH /report-cards/:id`
  (formTeacherComment, per-card) + `PUT /report-cards/arm/principal-note` (arm
  fan-out). Fan-out semantics visible at the URL.
- **Q6 Service split:** new `ReportCardWorkflowService` (transitions / release /
  reopen / comments), `ReportCardService` keeps build/read/render. Bank the
  service-per-concern pattern for slices 7–8 if they grow.
- **Q2 No auto-revert:** eager-set DRAFT→SUBJECT_REVIEWED on the sign-off
  cascade; NO down-transition on un-sign-off. form-review re-verifies
  (`isArmFullySignedOff`) so a stale SUBJECT_REVIEWED 409s there.
- **Q10 Comments optional** at form-review (empty/null is valid).
- **Q-reopen-stamps (cp2):** reopen clears formReviewedAt/By,
  principalApprovedAt/By, releasedAt; PRESERVES generatedAt/artifactUrl/pdfStatus
  (PDF stays on R2; re-release overwrites).
- **Banked tradeoff — snapshot drift:** the card rollup is FROZEN at build; live
  score edits in SUBJECT_REVIEWED/FORM_REVIEWED drift from it until a rebuild
  (via reopen). Workflow gates catch races via precondition re-checks but do NOT
  re-snapshot mid-workflow. **Pattern: a materialized snapshot in a workflow
  system is the audit truth at build/release time — it intentionally diverges
  from live data between those points.**

