- **cp3:** board state-change UI + comment UI + manual browser pass.

### cp1 build manifest
`packages/types/src/report-cards/workflow.dto.ts` (reportCardArmActionSchema +
ReportCardTransitionResultDto) → `report-cards/workflow/` module:
`transitions.ts` (LEGAL_FORWARD_TRANSITIONS + `assertAllInState` + 409s),
`released-guard.ts` (`assertNoReleasedCards`, plain fn), `subject-reviewed-cascade.ts`
(`isArmFullySignedOff` + `cascadeSubjectReviewedIfComplete`, plain fns),
`report-card-workflow.service.ts` (`formReview`, `approve`) → controller `POST
arm/form-review`, `POST arm/approve` → AssessmentService patched (gate on
createScore/updateScore/bulkUpsertScores/signOff/signOffColumn; cascade after
signOff/signOffColumn, same tx) → ReportCardService.build non-DRAFT guard.

- **No DI cycle:** the gate + cascade are plain FUNCTIONS imported by
  AssessmentService (whose module is imported by ReportCardsModule). The function
  files import only `@school-kit/db` + `@school-kit/types`, so the file graph is
  acyclic and there's no AssessmentModule ↔ ReportCardsModule provider cycle.
- **Audit:** report-card.form-review / report-card.approve, metadata
  { termId, classArmId, fromStatus, toStatus, cardCount }. The cascade writes NO
  audit (it rides on sign-off, which already audits).
- **Role gates:** form-review = owner/admin OR arm's form teacher (404 for a
  stranger teacher, mirrors assertCanReadArm); approve = owner/admin.

